30/06/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The government announced Tuesday (29 June) that Romania and Hungary will conduct joint customs control at the new border checkpoint at Sacuieni-Letavertes, which will be opened next week. Inauguration of the new checkpoint is set to coincide with a meeting between Romanian Prime Minister Adrian Nastase and his Hungarian counterpart, Peter Medgyessy, the first since Hungary became a full-fledged member of the EU in May. (Rompres - 30/06/04)
